      → \"cursor-agent\"\n  - \"+copilot@users.noreply.github.com\"            → \"github-copilot-agent\" (suffix match)\n  - \"+devin-ai-integration[bot]@users.noreply...\"  → \"devin\" (suffix match)\n  - \"noreply@anthropic.com\"                        → \"claude-web\"\n  - \"noreply@openai.com\"                           → \"codex-cloud\"\n  - \"roomote@roocode.com\"                          → \"roo-background\"\n\nAGENT_USERNAME_MAPPINGS: (username, platform)\n  - \"copilot-swe-agent[bot]\"     → \"github-copilot-agent\"\n  - \"devin-ai-integration[bot]\"  → \"devin\"\n  - \"cursor[bot]\"                → \"cursor-agent\"\n```\n\nWhen an agent commit is detected this way, `simulate_agent_authorship()` creates a synthetic `AuthorshipLog` treating all lines as AI-authored.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Mechanism for Attaching Notes to Commits\n\nThe core function is `notes_add()` in `/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/src/git/refs.rs` (line 13):\n\n```rust\npub fn notes_add(repo: &Repository, commit_sha: &str, note_content: &str) -> Result<(), GitAiError>\n```\n\nIt runs: `git notes --ref=ai add -f -F - <commit_sha>` with the note content on stdin. After writing, it fires the `post_notes_updated` hook.\n\nFor batch operations, `notes_add_batch()` (line 181) and `notes_add_blob_batch()` (line 254) use `git fast-import` with a handcrafted fast-import script — much faster than one call per commit.\n\nThe **flow** for a normal commit:\n\n1. **Pre-commit** (`/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/src/authorship/pre_commit.rs`): `pre_commit()` runs `checkpoint::run()` with `CheckpointKind::Human` if AI checkpoints exist. This snapshots the current working state into the working log.\n\n2. **Post-commit** (`/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/src/authorship/post_commit.rs`): `post_commit()` (called from `commit_post_command_hook`):\n   - Reads the working log for the parent commit SHA\n   - Calls `VirtualAttributions::from_just_working_log()` or `from_working_log_snapshot()`\n  