e** (Trace2-based, `/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/src/daemon.rs`) receives events from `GIT_TRACE2_EVENT` and processes checkpoints asynchronously.\n\n**User-facing `git_ai_hooks`** (`/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/src/authorship/git_ai_hooks.rs`):\n- `POST_NOTES_UPDATED_HOOK = \"post_notes_updated\"` — fired after every note write\n- Payload is JSON array of `{commit_sha, repo_url, repo_name, branch, is_default_branch, note_content}` sent via stdin\n- Commands run in parallel, wait up to 3 seconds, then detach\n\n**`install-hooks`** command (`/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/src/commands/install_hooks.rs`) installs the binary as the git wrapper for each detected AI agent (Cursor, Claude Code, Windsurf, Copilot, etc.), and also handles Trace2-based daemon setup.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Test Infrastructure\n\nThe test suite is in `/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/tests/integration/` with 80+ test modules.\n\n**Core test utilities:**\n\n- `/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/tests/integration/repos/test_repo.rs` — `TestRepo`: creates isolated git repos, wraps git commands through `git-ai` binary, handles daemon mode.\n- `/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/tests/integration/repos/test_file.rs` — `TestFile` + `ExpectedLineExt`: helpers to set file content with `.ai()` / `.human()` markers and assert blame attribution.\n- `/Users/johnw/src/git-ai/missing-notes/src/git/test_utils/mod.rs` — `TmpRepo`, `TmpFile`: unit test repo creation using `git2` (feature-gated behind `test-support`).\n\n**Test modes** (set via `GIT_AI_TEST_GIT_MODE`):\n- `wrapper` — default, uses git-ai as git wrapper\n- `daemon` — uses Trace2 background service\n- `wrapper-daemon` — both\n\n**Test macros** (in `repos/mod.rs`):\n- `subdir_test_variants!` — generates 4 variants per test: subdirectory, worktree, -C flag, -C flag+worktree\n- `worktree_test_wrappers!` — 3 variants: wrapper, daemon, wrapper-daemon in worktree\n- `reuse_tests_in_worktree!` — add worktree variants for ex